Tutorial: Edit Cells


Table of Contents

  • Python cells
  • Markdown cells
  • Delete cell
  • Copy cell
  • Reorder cells

Python cells

Back to Table of Contents

  • Select Insert .. Insert Cell Below (or Insert Cell Above)



  • Click on the cell type list.



  • Ensure that the cell type is Code



  • Enter a Python command like print( 'Hello world!' )
  • Select Run to execute the command(s) in the cell.
  • Check the cell outputs.



Markdown cells

Back to Table of Contents

  • Select Insert .. Insert Cell Below (or Insert Cell Above) (same as above)
  • Change the cell type to Markdown.



  • Enter Markdown code, like # This is a Heading
  • Select Run to display the Markdown code as HTML.



  • Verify that the displayed HTML looks correct.



Delete

Back to Table of Contents

  • Select a cell.
  • Select Edit .. Delete Cells



  • Verify that the cell has been deleted.



Copy

Back to Table of Contents

  • Select a cell.
  • Select Edit .. Copy Cells
  • Select Edit .. Paste Cells Above or Paste Cells Below



  • Verify that the cells have been copy & pasted.



Reorder

Back to Table of Contents

  • Select a cell
  • From the Edit menu, choose Move Cell Up or Move Cell Down



  • You can also use the or arrow buttons to move cells.



  • Verify that the cell has been moved.
